The meaning here given (it is practically that of Lipsius) is so easily derived from the analogous uses of the word, and is withal so eminently suitable to the sense of the passage, that the emendation of Ursinus, though accepted by Peter, Baehrens, and others, need not be considered seriously‚ the more so, as it is inconceivable how an original ‘corona' could ever have been corrupted into ‘cortina' For this word must have been unfamiliar, not to say unknown, to the scribes, at least in the sense which is here called for. —Baehrens' contention (Comm. crit. p. 75) that ‘vix'

ought to be placed before ‘quisquam’ is based upon a serious misinterpret- ation of the passage.
